            <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/txt_banner_title`, {
            text:'Provider App: Reducing Operational Fragmentation for Active Reservations',}) %>

            <h3>Helping QPs manage reservations, customer communication, and urgent updates on the go.</h3>

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>


    <div class="spacingMedium"></div>

    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--cols-3">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5><span class="fontWeight400">Role: </span>Lead UX Designer for V1 provider app strategy, research synthesis, workflow design, and scope prioritization</h5>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5><span class="fontWeight400">Scope: </span>Mobile provider operations console focused on reservation-centered communication, operational alerts, and urgent coordination workflows</h5>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5><span class="fontWeight400">Stakeholders: </span>VP Product Design, PM, CTO, engineering, QA, and active providers</h5>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="spacingXLarge"></div>
    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5 class="fontWeight400">Summary:</h5>

            <h5>Phase one focused on centralizing reservation-based communication, operational alerts, and daily coordination workflows into a mobile-first provider operations console.</h5>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5 class="fontWeight400">Expected impact:</h5>
            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li>Reduce missed operational updates</li>
              <li>Improve provider coordination clarity</li>
              <li>Reduce operational mental load</li>
              <li>Support scalable provider operations as marketplace supply grows</li>

            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section id="challenge" data-nav="challenge" class="banner_intro">

    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/divider25`, {
            sectionName:'Challenge',
            topSpacing:'spacingMedium',
            bottomSpacing:'spacingXLarge',
            topNbottomSpacing:''
            }) %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/txt_title_l`, {title:'Marketplace context',}) %>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5 class="fontWeight400">BabyQuip providers (QPs) manage:</h5>
            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li> reservations</li>
              <li> logistics</li>
              <li> customer coordination</li>
              <li> delivery timing</li>
              <li> operational planning</li>
            </ul>
            <h5 class="fontWeight400 greyBg400 greyBg200 border-radius paddingXS">👉 often while actively handling deliveries throughout the day.</h5>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5>The provider ecosystem continues growing, but operational coordination remained fragmented across:</h5>
            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li> email</li>
              <li> texting</li>
              <li> platform notifications</li>
              <li> reservation pages</li>
              <li> external notes/templates</li>
            </ul>
            <h5 class="fontWeight400 greyBg400 greyBg200 border-radius paddingXS">👉 our platform did not boost business operation much, they typically use external tool, crm, google sheet, google keep etc. they manage and planning bookings at night or the weekend</h5>

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>


    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/txt_title_l`, {title:'Why this matters',}) %>
            <h3>Operational friction limits provider scalability.</h3>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--cols-2">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5>As provider volume and reservation complexity increase:</h5>
            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li> communication becomes harder to track</li>
              <li> operational updates get buried</li>
              <li> overbooking risk increases </li>
              <li> coordination relies heavily on manual workarounds</li>
              <li> providers spend nights/weekends managing logistics manually</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5>As provider volume and reservation complexity increase:</h5>
            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li> Provider retention</li>
              <li> Fulfillment reliability</li>
              <li> Operational scalability </li>
              <li> Marketplace supply quality</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/txt_title_l`, {title:'Problem',}) %>
            <h3>Existing communication architecture fragmented operational workflows</h3>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5>The current provider experience mixed:</h5>
            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li> customer messages</li>
              <li> reservation updates</li>
              <li> platform announcements </li>
              <li> transfer offers</li>
              <LI> payment/system alerts</LI>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--cols-4">
          <div class="Grid-cell">
            <div class="element">
              <img class="modal-target card2026" src="legacy_notifications.png" alt="Current notifications screenshot">
              <h5>Current notifications</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="Grid-cell">
            <div class="element">
              <img class="modal-target card2026" src="legacy_messages.png" alt="Current messages screenshot">
              <h5>Current messages</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="Grid-cell">
            <div class="element">
              <img class="modal-target card2026" src="legacy_email_based_message_test.png" alt="Email-based message test">
              <h5>Email-based message test</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="Grid-cell">
            <div class="element">
              <img class="modal-target card2026" src="legacy_messages_notifications.png" alt="Messages acting as email wrapper and notification feed">
              <h5>Messages mixed with notifications</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5>inside disconnected inboxes and notification feeds.</h5>
            <h5>Meanwhile, platform messaging functioned primarily as an email wrapper rather than a reservation-centered communication system.</h5>
            <h5>Result:</h5>
            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li> important updates easy to miss</li>
              <li> operational attention fragmented</li>
              <li> providers moved communication off-platform into texting/email </li>
              <li> reservation coordination became difficult to track</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>



      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5 class="fontWeight400 greyBg400 greyBg200 border-radius paddingXS">👉 Main problem: QPs could not easily tell what needed attention, what was customer communication, and what was reservation-critical.</h5>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="insight" data-nav="insight">
    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <div class="blankHXXS"></div>
            <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/divider25`, {
            sectionName:'Insight',
            topSpacing:'spacingMedium',
            bottomSpacing:'spacingXLarge',
            topNbottomSpacing:''
            }) %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/txt_title_l`, {title:'Research & Discovery',}) %>

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h3 class="fontWeight400">Research Activities</h3>
            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li> Reviewed current provider workflows</li>
              <li> Tested existing notification/message systems directly</li>
              <li> Interviewed active QPs</li>
              <li> Mapped communication flows and operational behaviors</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>


      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h3 class="fontWeight400">Key Behavioral Findings</h3>
            <h5 class="fontWeight400 greyBg400 greyBg200 border-radius paddingXS">💡 Reservation is the primary object. Communication is secondary.</h5>

            <h5>QPs organize work around:</h5>
            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li>delivery timing</li>
              <li> reservation stages</li>
              <li> operational urgency</li>
              <li> logistics coordination</li>
            </ul>
            <h5>not around standalone message threads.</h5>

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h3 class="fontWeight400">QPs built external operational systems</h3>

            <h5>Providers relied on:</h5>
            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li> Gmail </li>
              <li> texting </li>
              <li> Google Keep templates </li>
              <li> manual scheduling</li>
              <li>personal workflow systems</li>
            </ul>
            <h5>to compensate for fragmented platform coordination tools.</h5>

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h3 class="fontWeight400">Messaging itself was not the core problem</h3>
            <h5>Email-based communication already supported many existing workflows successfully.</h5>
            <div class="spacingSmall"></div>
            <h5>The larger issue was:</h5>
            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li> operational fragmentation </li>
              <li> notification overload </li>
              <li> poor urgency hierarchy </li>
              <li> weak reservation-centered coordination </li>
            </ul>
            <h5>to compensate for fragmented platform coordination tools.</h5>

          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h5 class="fontWeight400 greyBg400 greyBg200 border-radius paddingXS">💡 Key insight: Providers were not struggling because they lacked another messaging channel. They were struggling because communication was disconnected from the reservation work it supported.</h5>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

  </section>

  <section id="strategy" data-nav="strategy">
    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <div class="blankHXXS"></div>
            <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/divider25`, {
            sectionName:'Strategy',
            topSpacing:'spacingMedium',
            bottomSpacing:'spacingXLarge',
            topNbottomSpacing:''
            }) %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/txt_title_l`, {title:'Initial exploration',}) %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h3 class="fontWeight400">Early exploration considered a broader provider app surface</h3>

            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li> calendar </li>
              <li> messaging </li>
              <li> notifications </li>
              <li> settings </li>
              <li>transfer management</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--cols-4">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <img class="modal-target card2026" src="wireframe.png" alt="wireframe">
            <h5>early wireframe/concept</h5>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <img class="modal-target card2026" src="wireframe.png" alt="wireframe">
            <h5>early wireframe/concept</h5>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <img class="modal-target card2026" src="wireframe.png" alt="wireframe">
            <h5>early wireframe/concept</h5>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <img class="modal-target card2026" src="wireframe.png" alt="wireframe">
            <h5>early wireframe/concept</h5>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">

        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h3 class="fontWeight400">But research and implementation discussions revealed:</h3>

            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li> messaging/notifications caused the highest operational friction </li>
              <li> scheduling behavior already existed externally </li>
              <li> backend/system complexity could significantly delay launch </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    </div>


    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/txt_title_l`, {title:'Design Principles',}) %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="wrapper">

      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--cols-2">

        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h3 class="fontWeight400">Anchor communication to reservations</h3>
            <h5>Reservation context remains persistent across messaging workflows.</h5>


          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h3 class="fontWeight400">Prioritize operational urgency over chronology</h3>
            <h5>Upcoming deliveries and urgent actions matter more than newest messages alone.</h5>

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--cols-2">

        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h3 class="fontWeight400">Reduce operational mental load</h3>
            <h5>Providers should quickly identify:</h5>

            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li> what needs attention </li>
              <li> what changed </li>
              <li> what is urgent </li>
              <li> what requires action </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h3 class="fontWeight400">Support real provider workflows</h3>
            <h5>The system acknowledges:</h5>

            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li> texting behavior </li>
              <li> email usage </li>
              <li> repeated templates </li>
              <li> operational batching workflows </li>
            </ul>
            <h5>instead of forcing fully in-app communication.</h5>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>





    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/txt_title_l`, {title:'V1 Strategy & Scope Definition',}) %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--cols-2">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h3 class="fontWeight400">Phase one focused on:</h3>

            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li> operational inbox </li>
              <li> reservation-centered communication </li>
              <li> urgency hierarchy </li>
              <li> notification organization </li>
              <li> quick operational actions</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h3 class="fontWeight400">Intentional scope reductions</h3>
            <h5>To improve feasibility and speed-to-launch:</h5>
            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li> calendar postponed</li>
              <li> signup flow removed from V1 </li>
              <li> full transfer management excluded</li>
              <li> existing email infrastructure preserved</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Grid-cell">
        <div class="element">
          <h5 class="fontWeight400 greyBg400 greyBg200 border-radius paddingXS">📌 Instead of rebuilding provider communication from scratch, the app focused on improving operational coordination around existing behaviors.</h5>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  


    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/txt_title_l`, {title:'Design principles',}) %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--cols-4">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h4 class="fontWeight400">Anchor communication to reservations</h4>
            <h5>Reservation context remains persistent across messaging workflows.</h5>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h4 class="fontWeight400">Prioritize operational urgency over chronology</h4>
            <h5>Upcoming deliveries and urgent actions matter more than newest messages alone.</h5>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h4 class="fontWeight400">Reduce operational mental load</h4>
            <h5>QPs should quickly identify what needs attention, what changed, what is urgent, and what requires action.</h5>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h4 class="fontWeight400">Support real provider workflows</h4>
            <h5>The system acknowledges texting, email usage, repeated templates, and operational batching instead of forcing everything in-app.</h5>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>


    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/txt_title_l`, {title:'Tradeoffs & Constraints',}) %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--cols-2">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h3 class="fontWeight400">Tradeoffs</h3>

            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li> preserved email-based messaging infrastructure for V1 </li>
              <li> texting remains external operational behavior </li>
              <li> full transfer workflows postponed </li>
              <li> availability management identified but deferred </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <h3 class="fontWeight400">Constraints</h3>
            <ul class="listCircle">
              <li> legacy backend systems</li>
              <li> provider operational variability </li>
              <li> implementation complexity</li>
              <li> mobile-first rollout priorities</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="solution" data-nav="solution">
    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <div class="blankHXXS"></div>
            <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/divider25`, {
            sectionName:'Solution',
            topSpacing:'spacingMedium',
            bottomSpacing:'spacingXLarge',
            topNbottomSpacing:''
            }) %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/txt_title_l`, {title:'V1 provider operations console',}) %>
            <h3>Phase one reframes provider messaging from a standalone communication feature into a reservation-centered operations console, helping QPs manage urgent updates, customer communication, and daily coordination with less fragmentation.</h3>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/txt_title_l`, {title:'Unified operational inbox',}) %>
            <h4>Messages, notifications, and reservation alerts are centralized into one operational inbox with pinned urgent actions, message counts, reservation-linked communication, category filters, and unread tracking.</h4>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/txt_title_l`, {title:'Reservation-centered messaging',}) %>
            <h4>Message threads keep reservation summary, delivery timing, quick access to reservation details, and operational status indicators close to the conversation.</h4>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/txt_title_l`, {title:'Operational prioritization',}) %>
            <h4>Inbox sorting prioritizes upcoming deliveries, urgent reservations, awaiting responses, and transfer approvals instead of relying only on chronological messaging behavior.</h4>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/txt_title_l`, {title:'Workflow efficiency',}) %>
            <h4>Quick templates and actions support repeated workflows such as delivery confirmation, airport coordination, gate code requests, and pickup reminders.</h4>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/txt_title_l`, {title:'Expected outcomes',}) %>
            <div class="marginLeft">
              <h5>· Fewer missed operational updates</h5>
              <h5>· Clearer reservation coordination</h5>
              <h5>· Reduced context switching</h5>
              <h5>· Improved provider workflow visibility</h5>
              <h5>· Stronger operational scalability</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="Grid Grid--gutters Grid--full Grid--gutter">
        <div class="Grid-cell">
          <div class="element">
            <%- include(`${templatePath}/shared/txt_title_l`, {title:'Future opportunities',}) %>
            <div class="marginLeft">
              <h5>· Availability management</h5>
              <h5>· Calendar integration</h5>
              <h5>· Deeper transfer workflows</h5>
              <h5>· Operational automation</h5>
              <h5>· Smarter urgency routing</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Case study ends -->
  <div class="blankHS"></div>
  <!-- Shared across the platform -->
